<p itemprop="description">Research methods involves designing and conducting systematic investigations to gather, analyze, and interpret information to inform decision-making and policy development in government contexts.</p>

<div class="proficiency-levels">
    <h2>Proficiency Levels</h2>

    <ol class="skill-levels">
        <li>
            <h3>Awareness</h3>
            <p>You can understand different research approaches and methodologies, and recognise the importance of evidence-based decision making in government.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h3>Working</h3>
            <p>You can conduct basic research activities, gather and analyze data using established methods, and contribute to research projects under guidance.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h3>Practitioner</h3>
            <p>You can design and execute comprehensive research projects, select appropriate methodologies, and produce high-quality research outputs that inform policy and practice.</p>
        </li>
        <li>
            <h3>Expert</h3>
            <p>You can lead research strategy, establish research frameworks and standards, and influence government policy through high-impact research and evidence.</p>
        </li>
    </ol>
</div>

